page.title: 15TWELVE,THE SQUARE,LEASINGHAM
page.content: 12,The Square was built in 1650 and was originally only the two downstairs but later an upstairs was built. It had an old wash_room with a fire_place and an old boiler for washing clothes and they are still there.There is an outside toilet because they did not have a bathroom.There is an old pig_sty for keeping the pigs until Sunday, when one would be killed and eaten for Sunday dinner.There was an old well some_where in the garden and it is thought to be buried under the long concrete path running downthe right hand side of the garden.
